# Truegrynd – Architecture & Folder Structure

## Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **Backend**: Supabase (auth, database, realtime)
- **State**: Zustand (global) + React Query (server state)
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod
- **UI primitives**: Radix UI
- **Tests**: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (e2e)

## Folder Structure

```
src/
├── app/                         # Next.js App Router pages & layouts
│   ├── (auth)/                  # Auth group: /login, /signup, /onboarding
│   ├── (app)/                   # Authenticated group: /arena, /clan, /profile
│   │   ├── arena/
│   │   ├── clan/
│   │   └── profile/
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   └── page.tsx                 # Landing / splash
│
├── features/                    # Feature modules
│   ├── auth/                    # Auth flow, onboarding, faction choice
│   ├── challenges/              # Challenge feed, challenge detail, creator studio
│   ├── leaderboard/             # Leaderboard display and filtering
│   ├── factions/                # Faction stats, clan tab
│   ├── profile/                 # User profile, history, trophies
│   └── finisher-card/           # Canvas card generation + share
│
├── components/                  # Shared UI primitives
│   └── ui/                      # Radix-based components (Button, Dialog, etc.)
│
├── hooks/                       # Shared hooks
│
├── lib/                         # Core infrastructure
│   ├── supabase.ts
│   ├── utils.ts
│   └── types/
│       └── database.types.ts
│
└── test/
    └── setup.ts
```

## Dependency Direction
```
app/ → features → components / hooks / lib
components → lib only
lib → nothing above it
```

## Key Rules
- Each feature folder has an `index.ts` exporting its public API
- Pages are thin — they assemble features, no business logic
- All Supabase calls live in `features/*/services/` or `lib/`
- Never import a feature from another feature — use shared lib or lift to app/
